direct ClassMetaobject constructor paired with a nested Fixture class. In native image scenarios, I wonder if the reflection config needs to include all public constructors, fields, and methods. I also need to consider how the agent generates this during runtime. It's a bit complex, but I'm working through it!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering reflection in testing**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how ClassMetaobject may reflect on the test fixture class, and whether the agent might need to capture dynamic access to that fixture. Is it possible that the native image requires reflective metadata for the fixture? Since test classes are app code but not always set up for reflection, I wonder if the native image would restrict Constructor.newInstance for test fixtures not included in the config. It might be worth inspecting the generated reflect config to clarify.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_6XKVrfTMJwubMNDTnJIViFAQ|fc_047b8ac2d3b385ed0169f50392224c81a3923b44df7cc38807", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/build/native -name '*reflect*' -o -name 'reflect-config.json' | head -20 && find tests/src/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/build -name 'reflect-config.json' -print | head"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3147, "output": 1392, "cacheRead": 29184, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33723, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777664892429, "responseId": "resp_047b8ac2d3b385ed0169f5037ce60c81a391d5b631dc8e692f"}}
